runDlg=I will see how you keep your promise.
finishDlg=Ho&#x2026;Already finished?  I like the way you speedly take care of your work. Claris has sent me a nice guy! Here is the right price for your job. I will tell the village people about it. Good work!
</newversion></questtextxml></warri002><sealv601><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Hunt Strong Kimukeu
desc=Recently, thanks to adventurers' help and the strong policy of our Lord, the activities of the Pirates of Black Dragon and the Pirates of Bloodsea have largely been reduced. But on the sea, monsters, which are just as dangerous as pirates, are still remaining. I mean monsters like Kimukeu.  A Strong Kimukeu&#x2019;s huge pincers is dangerous enough to shake the whole ship by only one collision. Most of them mainly live on the shortest route on the way to Magnel.
 Some days ago, two ships were nearly broken from just one attack of a Kimukeu. Therefore, I discussed with Jeremiah, who is running a trade post, and as the result, we decided to offer a reward for an adventurer who hunts them. How about it? Why don&#x2019;t you give it a try?
runDlg=You can find Strong Kimukeus on the shortest route connecting Cardiff and Magnel port. Just like Black Kimukeu, it is a monster that only attacks when it is close to you, so if you shoot it from a longer range, you can easily capture it.
finishDlg=Excellent job! I heard that they are also removing Strong Kimukeu in Magnel and we did reduce them quite much together. If we continue with it, trade activities will be kept active. Oh! Go to Jeremiah. He will pay you on this task. Also, you may hear about a strange place found recently.
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Hunt Fierce Kimukeu
desc=Recently, thanks to adventurers' help and the strong policy of our Lord, the activities of the Pirates of Black Dragon and the Pirates of Bloodsea have largely been reduced. But on the sea, monsters, which are just as dangerous as pirates, are still remaining. I mean monsters like Kimukeu.  A Fierce Kimukeu&#x2019;s huge pincers is dangerous enough to shake the whole ship by only one collision. Most of them mainly live on the shortest route on the way to Magnel.
 Some days ago, two ships were nearly broken from just one attack of a Kimukeu. Therefore, I discussed with Jeremiah, who is running a trade post, and as the result, we decided to offer a reward for an adventurer who hunts them. How about it? Why don&#x2019;t you give it a try?
runDlg=You can find Fierce Kimukeus on the shortest route connecting Cardiff and Magnel port. Just like Black Kimukeu, it is a monster that only attacks when it is close to you, so if you shoot it from a longer range, you can easily capture it.
finishDlg=Excellent job! I heard that they are also removing Fierce Kimukeu in Magnel and we did reduce them quite much together. If we continue with it, trade activities will be kept active. Oh! Go to Jeremiah. He will pay you on this task. Also, you may hear about a strange place found recently.
</newversion></questtextxml></sealv601></diff><settings><searchkey> questlistid</searchkey><ignore> id</ignore><columnnametable> </columnnametable><parsexml> </parsexml></settings></server_questtext_EN></number62><number63><server_questtext_ESP><diff><warri002><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Hunting Little Dodo
desc=Hmm. Estoy buscando a una persona pero no tengo prisa para contratar a nadie.

Como esto es para Roxbury, quiero que me demuestres tus habilidades. Tengo que saber si puedo confiar en ti. 

&#xBF;Puedes ver la entrada a mi derecha? Detr&#xE1;s de esas puertas se encuentra la zona llamada Weedridge. 

El numero de Dodos en Weedridge ha aumentado muy r&#xE1;pido. Por culpa de este aumento inesperado, est&#xE1;n atacado a los granjeros y la gente del pueblo. Si te encargas de los Little Dodos, confiar&#xE9; en ti... &#xBF;Que te parece? Tambi&#xE9;n te pagar&#xE9; un precio razonable si quieres.
runDlg=Espero que cumplas tu promesa. 
finishDlg=&#xBF;Has terminado? Me gusta la gente que trabaja duro. &#xA1;Claris me ha recomendado una persona estupenda! Aqu&#xED; tienes tu recompensa. &#xA1;Buen Trabajo!
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Hunting Dodo
desc=Hmm. Estoy buscando a una persona pero no tengo prisa para contratar a nadie.

